Text.Value: It said 'they're coming.' But... who?
Panic: is the Butler back? You almost feel his beady eye on your back.
It's never good news with a mysterious voice, is it? Always 'warning, demons', never 'warning, nymphs bathing nearby'.
You think of Shar - could she be speaking to you here at last, in the dark...?
Careful... If we can hear it, perhaps it can hear us...
Ignore the voice.
Control your thoughts. It seems I'm not the only one listening.
((*they're coming. you're coming*))
No, someone's coming. And someone else wants us to know...
No devils here. That's a myconid. And it seems to be warning us...
That voice... what was that?
Pray for fortitude against the mental trespass.
((*they're coming. you're coming*))
Hush. Do you hear it?
Tell me I'm not imagining that voice.
This might be some devil's ploy. Don't listen to it.
Still your thoughts to this new voice.
((*they're coming. they're coming*))
That voice... Do you hear it too?
No. And it's unlike any I've yet heard.
What in the Nine Hells is that?
Stay silent. Could Cazador have found you?
Such faculties of observation you possess! I'm ready, whatever's coming...
Who - what in the hells are you?
Something's coming - and if it lives down here in the dark, it won't be anything good.
Careful... If we can hear it, perhaps it can hear us...
Then control your thoughts, lest your mind be exploited.
Tell me you hear that voice.
It said 'they're coming.' But... who?
No, listen! A myconid... it's warning us.
((*more are coming*))
You listen all you want - but it can get the hells out of my head.
Still your mind to this unusual voice.
Fill your mind with the words of your oath. Drown out the voice.
That voice... it doesn't sound like the Urges. The Urges don't give warnings...
That's a myconid. And it's warning us...
No. Something's coming - and if it lives down here in the dark, it won't be anything good.
Well, when a creepy voice says 'something's coming', it's never good, is it?
Something is coming. Has a devil found me at last?

Synopsis: The party has heard a strange voice in their heads while exploring the depths of the Underdark They discuss it - is it their tadpole? A hallucination? Something else? They don't know.
